#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:10
msgid "Occurrence and Event datasets go through a series of steps when they are crawled and ingested by GBIF. The status of these pills for each dataset can be seen in the https://registry.gbif.org/dataset/search*GBIF Registry, and can be used to learn the cause of a dataset failing ingestion. The steps, also known as pills are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:12
msgid "The ingestion steps for occurrences are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "*XML TO VERBATIM*: Data coming from DIGIR/TAPIR endpoints is transformed to common internal verbatim format used by pipelines\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "*ABCD TO VERBATIM*: Data coming from ABCD format is transformed to common verbatim format used by pipelines\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "*DWCA TO VERBATIM*: Data coming from Darwin core archive format is transformed to common verbatim format used by pipelines\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "*VERBATIM TO IDENTIFIER*: Checking that identifiers (occurrenceIDs and triplets) in the dataset are unique and for an already published dataset it validates the number of identifiers that have been added/changed and fails the process if the number is above a threshold of 50%.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "*VERBATIM TO INTERPRETATION*: Data checking and enrichment, this step is responsible for persisting new identifiers (occurrenceID or triplet combinations.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "*INTERPRETED TO INDEX*: Indexing of data into search indexes to support search tools and some mapping functionality.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "*HDFS VIEW*: Loading of data into download infrastructure to allow the data to be downloaded through the API.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "*FRAGMENTER*: Loading of verbatim data into a database to support API access ,\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:23
msgid "For event datasets, there are three different EVENT versions indexing, interpretation and hdfsview steps, which do the same thing but for events:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "*EVENTS VERBATIM TO INTERPRETED*: Data checking and enrichment for events\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "*EVENTS INTERPRETED TO INDEX*: Indexing of event data into search indexes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "*EVENTS HDFS VIEW*: Loading of event data into download infrastructure\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:30
msgid "Each one of these steps can be in three possible states:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:32
msgid "COMPLETED: The process was successful"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:33
msgid "FAILED: The process started but didn't go through because it encountered an error"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:34
msgid "ABORTED: The job was interrupted or cancelled, usually refers to invalid identifiers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:36
msgid "Finally, you can review the full results of the pipelines in the public ElasticSearch logs, where there is detailed information for each part of the process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Re ingestion comments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:40
msgid "Related to those steps, the registry can be used to run specific steps in pipeline, and the available steps are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:42
msgid "Converting the dataset: Equivalent to XML, ABDC or DWCA to verbatim steps"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:43
msgid "Occurrence - main interpretation: Equivalent to re run VERBATIM TO INTERPRETATION"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:44
msgid "Occurrence - indexing: Equivalent to re run INTERPRETED TO INDEX"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:45
msgid "Occurrence - creating table files: Equivalent to run HDFS VIEW"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:46
msgid "Saving raw data fragments: Equivalent to run FRAGMENTER"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:47
msgid "Events - main interpretation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:48
msgid "Events - indexing:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:49
msgid "Events - creating table files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:51
msgid "There are two additional options to modify the running of steps, those are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:54
msgid "Use the latest successful attempt: Run the steps using the latest attempt instead of a new one Exclude event steps: Run the steps without using events"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:56
msgid "The suggested comment when you are using any of those steps is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Ingestion of Checklists and Metadata-only datasets "
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:61
msgid "Checklists and Metadata-only datasets do not have these steps, because those are specific for indexing occurrences. For checklist it will show ‘processStateChecklist: FINISHED’. If they are pills present for a checklist, it is because it has the occurrence extension and the pills relate to that extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:65
msgid "For Metadata it will show “finishReason: NORMAL processStateOccurrence: EMPTY processStateChecklist: EMPTY”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-processing/modules/ROOT/pages/ingestion-pills.adoc:66
msgid "If there is a problem with one of those kind of datasets and the finishReason is: ABORT. You can review the full results of the pipelines in the Log option, that will redirect to the ElasticSearch results that have detailed information about ingestion."
msgstr ""

